'''''Rockerilla''''' is a monthly Italy-based music and cinema magazine founded in 1978.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockerilla.com/?page_id=652|title=Rockerilla: About Us|work=Rockerilla|date=2011|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref> It has collaborated with, among others, Richard Bertoncelli<ref>{{cite book|author=Riccardo Bertoncelli|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Improvisation_Identity_and_Tradition_Exp.html?id=wozYbXvkgqEC|title=Paesaggi immaginari: trent'anni di rock e oltre|publisher=Giunti Editore|date=January 1, 1998|page=13|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref> and [[Guido Chiesa]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0Ale8Osvs-8C&dq|title=Cinema e video a Torino 1992|publisher= Performing Arts|year=1992|page=12|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref> According to Federico Guglielmi, ''Rockerilla'' was followed by those most passionate about new trends in rock music in the early 1980s.<ref>{{cite book|author=Federico Guglielmi|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SlUq6M_LXXIC&dq|title=A denti stretti: la vera storia dei Litfiba |publisher=Giunti Editore|year=2000|pages=22â€“23|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref>

The headquarters of Rockerilla is in [[Cairo Montenotte]].<ref>{{cite book|author1=Alessandro Bonini|author2=Emanuele Tamagnini|title=Annuario della musica. 2006-2007|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hb1_I4bPQwoC&pg=PA140|accessdate=July 8, 2016|year=2006|publisher=Gremese Editore|isbn=978-88-8440-396-4|page=140}}</ref> The magazine covers genres ranging from [[New wave music|new wave]], [[hard rock]], [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]], [[punk rock]], and [[grunge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zoominfo.com/s/#!search/profile/company?companyId=350645687&targetid=profile|title=Rockerilla|work=ZoomInfo|date=2014 |accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref>

